      • getArity

        public int getArity()
        Description copied from interface: SetTerm
        Returns the arity of the tuples contained in this set. If the arity is one, then the set described by the set term only contains ''normal'' entities, otherwise tuples of higher arity. If the set terms do not agree on their arity, this method throws an IllegalStateException.
        Specified by:
        getArity in interface SetTerm
        Returns:
        Arity of tuples contained in set, or 1 if set elements are not tuples
